<Author>Justraveling
<Content>Good little hotel The Ludwig van Beethoven is a great hotel for those on a budget, yet wanting something clean and suitable for couples or families.We had a triple room, a really good size, small bathroom but separate toilet, so made it easier.The room was quite warm because of the afternoon sun, we asked for a fan, it was delivered to the room without any fuss.The breakfast is probably one of the best we've had at a similar three star hotel in Europe - great variety including cereals, fresh fruit and pastries, all served in a bright, airy room overlooking a pretty coutyard.The staff were really helpful with giving directions, suggestions for restaurants, etc. There is a wonderful Vietnamese restaurant just a few doors away, don't miss it, also a good Greek restaurant nearby.The subway and buses are really close to the hotel, it takes a while to get to the city but it's a nice experience by bus, you get to see so much of the suburbs.There are supermarkets and cafes all within a few hundred metres of the hotel.I would recommend this hotel to anyone who is happy to be a little bit away from the sights, but wants a clean, comfortable experience. 
