<Author>Kiwichick17
<Content>Great Breakfast We stayed at the Ludwig Van Beethoven in May of 2007. The hotel was excellent and definitely exceeded my expectations having stayed in some *interesting* places in Europe previously. Arriving at the hotel via the very closeby U7/U8 lines it was easy to get to and had a 24 hr reception. The staff all spoke english and were very helpful the entire time of our stay - helping us to track down a pub showing a particular sporting event and answering several queries.The hotel room was very clean and large with a great shower. Every morning there was a huge buffet breakfast spread out from 7am - 10am. This included salmon, parma ham, other meat cuts, a variety of cheeses, fruit, cereals etc. (This was included as part of our booking although I believe that they sometimes charge this separately).Near the hotel are numerous shops including a large department store, a supermarket (be warned it does not take credit cards), and several restaurants. I would definitely recommend the Vietnamese place just along from the hotel (Hamy Cafe). We just ordered the specials off the board which were delivered within about 2 minutes and were incredibly tasty.I would not hesitate to reccomend this hotel and would definitely stay there if visiting Berlin again. 
